replies.body:
@Repertoir, if I may, what's the logic behind throwing Dead Mans plate on live IMMEDIATELY after Bilgewater event, without testing it's repercussions a bit more on PBE? Despite disliking tanks, I have to admit, it's a very solid and interesting item. But it pretty much contradicts the "immobile juggernauts" thing you're working on atm. I've faced a few Dead Mans plates, and it's very scary seeing potent fighters simply run at you way faster than you can outrun them (cfr. immobile ADCs like Kog, or utility lacking ADCs like Lucian) and they get the shiv-like damage on top of it... Any comments you can give?
For clarification, this is not me simply hatetalking the item, I'm just curious as to why this happened like it did without additional testing concerning upcoming Juggernaut changes.

Grtz, Skip
